event_title:
The Diverse Universe of Touhou Fanworks 
and Fan-Creations
event_description: Join us for a deep dive into several popular Touhou fanworks and analyze on what makes them tick. We’ll cover a wide range of different works just as Reireimu, KKHTA and more!

event_title:
Even A Monkey Can Draw Anime Girls: 
How Touhou 1draw Can Boost Your Drawing Skills!
event_description: Do you look at pretty Touhou art on social media and feel a sense of creative envy? Did you stop drawing in high school and now, years later, you regret it? Jenn did too, until she found the solution to her woes: Touhou 1draw, an online drawing game created by Japanese Touhou artists. Jenn will explain her past struggles with learning to draw, what Touhou 1draw is and how it helped her improve, and invite the audience to join her for a Touhou 1draw session! (20 minute presentation, 1 hour drawing session)

event_title:
Gensokyo You Can! Moriya Shrine: 
The Gateway to Touhou Pilgrimage
event_description:
You dreamed about going to a Touhou Pilgrimage. How do you decide where to visit? Did you know 
Lake Suwa is an excellent choice?

In this panel, I hope to inspire you to visit a place of Touhou reference through a tour of the locale and
culture that inspired the Residents of the Moriya Shrine.

event_title:
Touhou M-1 Grand Prix: 
Translating on Lunatic
event_description:
Take a peek behind the curtain of Touhou M-1 Grand Prix's English translation to learn about the fun and challenges 
of localizing comedy. See what goes into making a Japanese work both understandable and enjoyable to English 
speakers.

event_title:
The Secret Sealing Club Panel: 
Magic, Mystery, and Merryment
event_description:
Touhou Creators Megapig9001 (Dreamweaver, Bad Apple Explained, Sealing Song) and Aeon (Lensed Night Sky, 
I Love Not Thinking, Yukari) dive into the world of Touhou's Secret Sealing Club (the CDs with Merry and Renko). 
Designed for both those who already love the Sealing Club and those who want to learn: this panel will take you 
through an intro to the club, mini-analyses of all the CDs, an overview of fanworks, speculation on the upcoming CD,
and the panel presenter's personal connection to Hifuu.
TouhouFest's Sunday start time is 9:00AM.
Here comes a returning guest of honor, TAMUSIC!!!! He'll be performing with us again this year at TouhouFest 2024 with his signature violin!
An opportunity to meet + get to know TAM himself and get autographs as desired!
Thank you all for attending TouhouFest 2024! MikoTan and others on staff will give a few closing remarks.

event_title: Beyond the Boundary: Underground Touhou Doujin Music
event_description:
Gaze at what lies beyond. A look into  the obscured yet endlessly vast underground scene of Touhou doujin music
 fanwork, and a primer to discover and support the circles which make it all happen!

Paradarx presents Touhou Wrestling! A few recorded rounds using the WWE 2K22 game to have custom characters 
duke it out with one another!

Phantasmagoria of Flower View is THE BEST Touhou game you've neglected to give a chance. You need a different mindset coming in, 
thankfully, help is here, as I (Suwawako), will help teach you the basic ins-and-outs, fun things and weird tidbits about this weird game no
one seems to praise. I might even change your mind too

event_title: Touhou Fan Game Jam: Alway Rember Sleep
event_description:
Introducing the Touhou Fan Game Jam community ([Discord here](https://discord.gg/touhougamejam)) and the regularly held Touhou Fan Game Jams 
and Touhou Pride Game Jams. In addition to covering why people attempt to make games in 72 hours and how the events work, we will 
explore adjacent topics such as the development of jam games post-jam, the Touhou indie gamedev scene, and our individual journeys as
game developers.

event_title: Touhou Luna Nights Any% Speed Run
event_description:
A speedrun of one of the most popular Touhou fangames of all time, the  run will complete the base game up to Flandre's 
fight in less than 50 minutes, without utilizing any major glitches or skipping sections of  the game.

event_title: The Weird World of PC-98 Touhou
event_description: An overview of the five games in the PC-98 era of Touhou, discussing the characters, gameplay, and story.

event_title: Reading the Moon: How to fully appreciate Silent Sinner in Blue
event_description:
Have you tried to get into Bougetsushou (Silent Sinner in Blue and Cage in Lunatic Runagate) but couldn't enjoy it? Or 
have you wanted to read it, but never got around to it? This panel is intended to set the stage for the series, introducing 
the mythological background and inspirations ZUN used for the works. Learn why Toyohime is depicted with sharks, 
why there are rabbits on the moon, why Reimu thinks Okuninushi is "handsome," and more!
